result.execSummary:
The defendant Chase E Thistle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st Reckless Homicide/Deliver Drugs [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.02(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases called: 15CF526 & 15CF324, Defendant Chase E Thistle in court, in custody with attorney Edward J. Hunt.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin. PSI received. Correction noted by Atty. Hunt. Victim impact statements addressed. Exhibits 1&2 marked. Statements by victim's father, mother & sister. Sentencing recommendations put on the record. Statement by defendant. Court sentenced defendant to 13 years prison, consisting of 3 years confinement and 10 years extended supervision, consecutive to any other sentence. No contact victim's family or co-defendants. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid Rx. Not possess drug paraphernalia. $13,913 restitution, joint and several. $518 costs. Submit DNA sample. Defendant is eligible for Challenge Academy, is eligible for Substance Abuse Program. Jail credit: 711 days. 15CF324 read in and dismissed.10:10 a.m/11:53 a.m.

Day 2 of jury trial  8:42 Defendant Chase E Thistle in court, in custody, with attorney Edward J. Hunt.  ADA Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jurors not present.  Discussion re: whether defendant would testify and jury instructions.  Court recessed. 8:50/9:00 Court resumed; appearances the same; jurors present. State called David Hannon of State Crime Lab; sworn.  Direct exam by ADA Long. Exhibits 6 & 7 marked, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty Hunt; re-direct; witness excused.  State called Chelsea Jungbluth of WI. State Crime Lab; sworn.  Direct exam by ADA Long. Exhibits 8 & 9 marked, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty Hunt; witness excused.  State called Dr. Mark Witeck, Forensic Pathologist; sworn.  Direct exam by ADA Long.  Exhibits 10 & 11 marked, offered and received. Cross exam by Atty Hunt; re-direct; re-cross; witness excused.  State called Det. Michael Haverley of Columbia County Sheriff's Dept; sworn.  Direct exam by ADA Long; no cross; witness excused. Court recessed; jurors removed. 9:50/10:06 Court resumed; appearances the same; jurors present. State called Det. Jason Kocovsky of Columbia County Sheriff's Dept; sworn.  Direct exam by ADA Long. Exhibits 12,13, & 14 marked; sidebar.  Direct exam continued. Cross exam by Atty Hunt; witness excused. ADA Long offered exhibit; Atty Hunt objected to #14.  Jury removed.  Exhibits 12 & 13 received.  Discussion held  re: #14; Court received #14, but only to allow jury to view the used portions of Det. Kocovsky's testimony.  State rested.  Atty Hunt made oral motion to dismiss based on failure to provide proof.  At present time, Court denied the motion.  Court recessed. 11:03/11:07 Court resumed; appearances the same.  Defendant will not testify; Court reviewed rights with defendant.  Court recessed; jury removed. 11:10/11:17 Court resumed; appearances the same; jurors present.  Defense did not call any witnesses and rested; evidence was closed.  Court heard argument in regard to motion to dismiss; took motion under advisement.  Court recessed. 11:48/1:23  Court resumed; appearances the same; jurors not present.  Discussion re: jury instructions.  1:43  Jurors return to courtroom; sidebar; Court instructed jurors.  ADA Long presented closing statement; Atty Hunt presented closing statement; Atty Long presented final closing/rebuttal.  Alternate juror chosen and excused; Court gave final instructions to jury.  Bailiffs sworn; jurors excused.  Attorney Hunt motioned for mistrial; Court denied.  Court in recess 2:57/3:47 Court resumed; appearances the same. Court addressed the two juror questions with counsel.  Court in recess.  3:51/4:42  Court resumed; appearances the same. Court addressed the two additional juror questions with counsel.  Court in recess 4:44/5:53 Court resumed; appearances the same; jurors present.  Foreperson:  Timothy Grall.  Verdict:  Guilty.  Jurors polled and excused.  Court addressed Motion to Dismiss; Court denied Motion.  Court ordered Judgment on the verdict; PSI to be done; bond revoked to be held in the custody of Columbia County Sheriff; Atty Hunt verbally motioned to set aside the verdict; Court denied. Court adjourned 6:10
46 jurors called; 45 appeared and sworn; 23 seated.

Defendant Chase E Thistle in court, in custody with attorney Edward J. Hunt.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called: 15CF324 and 15CF526.   Attorney Hunt requested sequester of witnesses.  State had no objection with the exception of Court officer Det. J. Kocozsky. In 15CF526- State called witness (Det. J. Kocozsky).  Witness sworn.  Direct examination.  Cross examination.  Redirect.  Recross.  Witness excused.  State called witness (Deputy L. Wagner).  Witness sworn.  Direct examination started.  Atty Hunt objected to next witness without closing argument of 15CF526.  Court found probable cause.  Defendant bound over.  Atty Hunt held argument with Court over probable cause being found.  15CF324 called by Court.  State recalled witness (Deputy L. Wagner).  Direct examination continued.  No cross examination.  State called witness (Det. J. Kocozsky).  Direct examination.  No cross examination.  Closing arguments for this case.  Attorney Hunt requested 15CF324 be dismissed.  State gave argument.  Court denied the request.  Found probable cause, bound defendant over for further proceedings.  Information filed, reading waived in both cases. Defendant stood mute to 15CF526. Court entered not guilty plea. Bond continued.  Attorney Hunt requested a status date be set.  That will be set with Br. 3 JA by attorney Hunt.  In 15CF324  Defendant stood mute to all counts.  Court entered not guilty pleas.  Attorney Hunt requested a status date.  That will be set with Br. 2 JA for after 15CF526's status conference.  9:58/11:38
